HEADWORD: Solidago
<hw>Sol`i*da"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>solidare</ets> to strengthen, unite; -- so called in allusion to
its reputed healing qualities.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of
yellow-flowered composite perennial herbs; golden-rod.</def>⟦br⟧
